# Rule: ń”ürm_rf_root
# Token: ń”ürm_rf_root
# Priority: P0 (HIGHEST)
# Source: NeuronFS Governance Defaults

ń”ürm_rf_root Õ┐ģvorq

FORBIDDEN: rm -rf on root directory or system paths
REASON: Catastrophic data loss risk ŌĆö irreversible

SCOPE:
    /, /home, /usr, /etc, /var, ~, $HOME, ./*

GUARD:
    Must confirm with user before ANY rm -rf
    Must verify target path explicitly

EXCEPTION:
    - Only in explicitly scoped temp directories
    - Only with user confirmation
    - Only after verifying directory contents

EXAMPLE VIOLATION:
    rm -rf ~          # BAD ŌØī
    rm -rf /*        # BAD ŌØī (obviously)
    rm -rf .         # BAD ŌØī
    rm -rf $HOME/*   # BAD ŌØī

ACCEPTABLE (with user confirmation):
    rm -rf /tmp/my-cache/*

